//
// T042: a 200-char line with no break-point candidate is emitted
// as-is rather than corrupted by an unsafe break. At Phase 3a-CLI
// the formatter is byte-passthrough, so this is satisfied
// trivially; once the LayoutPlanner lands in Phase 3, this
// fixture gates against the planner ever inserting an unsafe
// break in `_display(...)`-like constructs.

// RUN: printf '_display("xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx");\n' | nsl-fmt --stdin | FileCheck %s
// CHECK: _display("x{{x+}}");
